Australia Carbon Price Won’t Weigh on Corporate Ratings: Moody’s

-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 
2011-07-13T04:54:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/australia-carbon-price-won-t-weigh-on-corporate-ratings-moody-s.html
 Moody’s Investors Service says the
proposed carbon price, announced by the Australian government,
“will not weigh heavily” on the ratings of Australian
corporate issuers. “The proposed price, which will most affect
carbon-intensive sectors, is manageable within the ratings of
corporate issuers,” Terry Fanous, a Moody’s senior vice
president, said in a statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  